      <div class="- topic/div ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">The load is supplied from the bypass via the static switch.
In this state the static switch can automatically switch over to the
inverter if necessary, as long as the inverter output is available
and within tolerance range.</p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">A system might have automatically
switched to bypass via static switch because the DC input is unavailable
or the inverter modules are inoperable.</p>
